[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" gmbt_prlx_bg_type="parallax" gmbt_prlx_break_parents="0" gmbt_prlx_smooth_scrolling="" gmbt_prlx_video_mute="" gmbt_prlx_video_force_hd="" gmbt_prlx_opacity="100" gmbt_prlx_video_aspect_ratio="16:9" gmbt_prlx_parallax="none" gmbt_prlx_speed="0.3" gmbt_prlx_enable_mobile="" css=".vc_custom_1433940395801{background-image: url(http://www.highgradelab.com/sage/sushi/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/06/japanese_background.png?id=870) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}"][vc_column][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1433940250169{padding-top: 150px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="2/3"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

EXPERIENCE THE BEST FOOD,

MEET OUR CHEFS

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1433940420966{padding-top: 50px !important;padding-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][hgr_advimage hgr_advimage_image="720" hgr_advimage_overlaycolor="rgba(255,148,109,0.9)" hgr_advimage_overlaytextcolor="#ffffff" hgr_advimage_overlaycontent="I knew what I wanted to do from an early age. As young as 10, I remember telling schoolteachers: I will one day become a sushi chef like my father. I was given a part-time job at the restaurant when I was 16. But I was not allowed anywhere near a sushi knife - I was mostly cleaning or washing dishes. When I turned 18 - in 1964, an exciting year, with the Tokyo Olympics - I graduated and moved to Kobe to work as a trainee in a sushi restaurant. It was a good experience living and working in a different place, away from the family business. I learnt a lot and I enjoyed it."][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][hgr_advimage hgr_advimage_image="722" hgr_advimage_overlaycolor="rgba(255,148,109,0.9)" hgr_advimage_overlaytextcolor="#ffffff" hgr_advimage_overlaycontent="My father opened a sushi restaurant in Ginza in 1935. During the Second World War, my family escaped to my father's northern hometown in Akita, and this was where I was born in March 1945. It was a difficult time to be born. We stayed in Akita until 1946, when my father returned to Tokyo and reopened the sushi shop. We lived in the same building as the restaurant so it was where I grew up. I was surrounded by sushi from the start."][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][hgr_advimage hgr_advimage_image="721" hgr_advimage_overlaycolor="rgba(255,148,109,0.9)" hgr_advimage_overlaytextcolor="#ffffff" hgr_advimage_overlaycontent="I enjoy doing this, perhaps because I grew up in the same environment. My parents worked very hard - my father at the sushi bar and my mother serving tea and talking to customers. I watched this unfold every day. I had a strong respect for my parents and learnt a lot from them, especially my father, who had very famous customers, including prime ministers and artists. I normally finish around 22:30. It's a long day. But Sunday is always off, as the shop is closed, and during golf season, I sometimes play during the week."][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1433940359687{padding-bottom: 150px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

YOSUKE AKITA

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1446036572099{margin-top: -20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]

I was given a part-time job at the restaurant when I was 16. But I was not allowed anywhere near a sushi knife - I was mostly cleaning or washing dishes.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

IMADA KYUBEI

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446036578767{margin-top: -20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]

Me and my family we lived in the same building as the restaurant so it was where I grew up. I was always surrounded by sushi from the start.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left"]

SIKIYABASHI ONO

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446036583043{margin-top: -20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]

I had a strong respect for my parents and learnt a lot from them, especially my father, who had very famous customers, including prime ministers.
